s, students, and policy makers in criminal justice, sociology, and social services, Journeys shares stories that hope to inspire other victims and survivors while illuminating the different paths to resiliency and growth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aAbused womenzUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aIntimate partner violencezUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aPosttraumatic growthzUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aResilience (Personality trait) 0aResilience (Personality trait). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  abattered women.  acriminology.  aemotional abuse.  agendered abuse.  agendered violence.  aintimate partner abuse.  aintimate partner violence.  aipa.  aipv.  apaths to survivorship.  apost traumatic effect of intimate partner violence.  apost traumatic growth.  asocial science.  asocial service.  asurviving abuse.  asurviving abusive relationships.  asurviving domestic abuse.  asurviving intimate partner violence.  asurviving rape.  awomens agency.  awomens narratives of survival.  awomens resistance to violence.  awomens studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052028608540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961463423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961463/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles